_:N4f8b26d8d4ec42fea327545e575e2c37 <http://schema.org/description> "The UK Competition Appeal Tribunal (CAT) is a specialist judicial body with a cross-disciplinary expertise in law, economics, business and accountancy, whose function is to hear and decide cases involving competition or economic regulatory issues. CAT is a tribunal of the Department for Business and Trade ." .
